data.content:
Động từ
(khẩu ngữ, đùa) nhả ra
you owe me £5, come on, disgorge!
cậu nợ tớ 5 bảng, nhả ra mà trả đi chứ!
disgorge something [from something]
nôn ra; khạc ra
she was trying hard to disgorge a fish bone
chị ta cố khạc cái xương cá ra
disgorge(itself) into something
đổ ra (nói về sông ngòi)
the Mississippi disgorges (itself) into Gulf of Mexico
sông Mississippi đổ ra vịnh Mexico
disgorge from something(into something)
đổ ra, xô ra, tuôn ra
crowds disgorged from the theatre into the dark street
đám đông đổ từ nhà hát ra đường phố tối mịt

verb
-gorges; -gorged; -gorging
[+ obj] somewhat formal :to empty whatever is in the stomach through the mouth
The cat coughed and then disgorged [=(more commonly) vomited, threw up] a wad of hair.
[+ obj] :to let out or release (something)
We watched the airplane disgorging its passengers at the gate.
The damaged ship disgorged thousands of gallons of oil into the bay.
[no obj] :to flow out
The river disgorges into the ocean just south of the city.
